    <note class="who-knew" id="note-00012">
    <title>The Origin of the Metric System</title>
    <para id="para-00053">The metric system is the official measurement system for every country in the world except the United States, Liberia, and Myanmar. But did you know it originated in France during the French Revolution in the late 18th century? At the time there were over 250,000 different units of weights and measures in use, often determined by local customs and economies. For example, land was often measured in days, referring to the amount of land a person could work in a day.</para>
    </note>
    <note class="video" id="note-00013">
    <para id="para-00054"><link url="https://openstax.org/r/Metric_System_Matters">Why the Metric System Matters</link></para>
    </note>
    </section>
